              "focus": "evaluate_create",
              "difficulty_band": "mastery",
              "excerpt": "I thought that it looked more beautiful than the Moon dust in which Neil and I were leaving our footprints. I took out the American flag from the compartment where it was stored.",
              "stem": "If Buzz could write a letter to his ten-year-old self riding his bike across the George Washington Bridge, what message would he want to send? Use clues from the text.",
              "choices": {
                "A": "\"Stop riding bikes because they are dangerous.\"",
                "B": "\"Keep being independent and determined, because those qualities will help you reach the Moon someday.\"",
                "C": "\"Give up your dreams because they are too hard.\"",
                "D": "\"Never collect rocks because they are too heavy.\""
              },
